metadata.name: ATHENA #1
metadata.description: Athena is the goddess of intelligence, art, strategy, inspiration and peace in Greek mythology.  In Roman mythology, she is called Minerva.  His father is Zeus, the head of the gods, and his mother is Metis, the goddess of wisdom, the first wife of Zeus.  Its symbols are the shield, spear, olive branch and owl.  The spear represents war, the olive branch represents peace, and the sky-eyed owl represents wisdom.  Athena is the chief goddess and protector of the city of Athens, the city got its name from her.  Athena and the characters she symbolizes exist in similar forms in many cultures.  Athena also helped the Achaeans in the Trojan War and helped build the wooden horse.  Athena carries a special shield.  This shield is called Aegis.  On the shield, there is a picture of Medusa's head with different ornaments.
